oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Pulaski town square on Mule Day
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the east side of the town square in Pulaski, possibly taken on Mule Day. The square is crowded with people and carts along the storefronts. People can also be seen standing in the windows above Buggie's Iron & Hardware store.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Plazas; Stores & shops
